There was a oil filter report on the net about a year ago. This guy took
every known filter available , cut it open and inspected them for quality.
His site got shut down by the big filter makers for saying the truth.
His results were unbiased. NAPA gold filters one of the best along with MANN
(germany). I use MANN filters and have never had one blow or leak. BOSCH
wasn't on his list so there are no test results. I will post this to the
other list to see if anybody saved his site. There is still a link to it in
a round about way to avoid more lawsuits.
 
ronnie
 
ps. The mann filter I use has an internal bypass pressure release so it will
bypass the filter part under extreme pressures
 
 
